{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id0de400fe-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4072"},"text":"§ 4072.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"As used in this subchapter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0de400ff-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “secondary school” means a public school which provides secondary education as determined by State law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0de40100-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “sponsorship” includes the act of promoting, leading, or participating in a meeting. The assignment of a teacher, administrator, or other school employee to a meeting for custodial purposes does not constitute sponsorship of the meeting.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0de40101-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “meeting” includes those activities of student groups which are permitted under a school’s limited open forum and are not directly related to the school curriculum.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0de40102-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s4072/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “noninstructional time” means time set aside by the school before actual classroom instruction begins or after actual classroom instruction ends.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id0de40103-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/377/tVIII/s803"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–377, title VIII, § 803","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-08-11"},"text":"Aug. 11, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1303"},"text":"98 Stat. 1303","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
